17/02/2021

Deep learning in biology

Paper: Selene: a PyTorch-based deep learning library for sequence data by Kathleen M. Chen et al.

Introduction

Selene:

  • open-source software
  • python framework
  • development of deep learning models for any biological sequence data
  • software development kit + CLI
  • designed both for biologists and programmers

Some solutions already exist:

  • DragoNN (predictive modelling in genomics)
  • pysster (CNNs for sequence data)
  • Kipoi (archive, use and build of predictive models)

Main features

  • train already published model on new data
  • modify already published model architecture
  • evaluate abovementioned models

Use case

Use case

How Selene makes model training easier

  • automatically generates training, testing, and validation samples from the provided input data
  • partitions can be save so that comparisons across models can be done
  • automatically generates all results plots
  • models can be saved to Kipoi model zoo
